Definition: There will be a list of integer lists displayed. The values for each item in each internal list must be added up. The output will be a longest internal list.

Positive Examples.explanation: The output is the list containing the sum of the input index values placed in the same index
the sum of the index values in the list of lists gives the output

Negative Examples.explanation: The sum of each individual list is returned. So this is a bad example.
The output is the length of the smallest inner list. It should be the length of the longest inner list So this is a good example.
